<br>
Advanced combat &quot;feats&quot;  where one could do something other than just X damage would be nice to see, however we have procs which are essentially the same thing however random and crippling they are to rely upon.<br>
<br>
/disc I belive was the VI attempt to add depth to melee combat beond attack on and pushing ( flying )kick/backstab every 6 seconds and we all know how well thought out those were <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Really if you think about it VI fluxed up melee combat from the start and there isn't a damned thing they can do about it now without scrapping it and starting over. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kess0n>Kess0n</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/9/02 2:57:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2450.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://link.freepichosting.com/image.cgi/10723/0.jpg?x=60&y=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I want your opionion</span><hr size=1> Solution 1 is better and will probably be easier to implement anyway than a line of stamina using spells. I want to tank. I'm pretty sure 100% of the warriors out there want to tank as well. I don't want to slow, I don't want to snare, I don't want to debuff or anything. I just want to tank and be the best at it. <br>
<br>
Increased skills, improved HP boosts throughout 60-65, an AA that increases taunt abiltity maybe? Or an AA that increases the effect of STA or STR? A CS/CA warrior only AA? I'm surprised that the tanking AAs are given to just about everyone.<br>
<br>
There are enough concepts and various abilities out there. If I wanted them, I would start the class that has them. I wanted taunt, I wanted AC, I wanted HP, I wanted damage mitigation and I wanted weapons and armor so I started a warrior. Increasing those abilities is the right way to go.<br>
<br>
Adding gimmicks while leaving the lacking abilities we already have to rot is the temporary solultion and will make warriors what they are not. <br>
<br>
Plus it's highly unrealistic. I doubt you will log in one day and find out you have a spell bar. Increased skill caps and new AAs are possible and have happened before. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farlanderb>FarlanderB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/9/02 10:32:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2450.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I want your opionion</span><hr size=1> Warriors do not need to be fixed with AA skills.<br>
If Verant gives warriors spells, I'm quitting EQ. <p>[61 Warlord]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Farlander</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Human)<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->[32 Enchanter] <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Fainel</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (High Elf)<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> [1 Paladin]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> Sabern</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Half Elf)<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guild-legerdemain.com">Legerdemain</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - &quot;More with Less&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valdicoor>valdicoor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/9/02 11:02:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2450.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I dont think it will ever happen</span><hr size=1> The game has gone to hell in a handbasket in reference to 'balancing'.Things will never be truely balanced again, too many folks with their parse logs and DPS numbers from fights that last 3.5 hours. Its gone past being a game of characters and quests to a gripe session with Underpowered_class_01 complaining that the logs indicate that someone else out damaged them in the thirteenth minute of a 2 hour fight. I will admit it would be nice to see my character take and deal damage as well as i see he should, it wont happen, its not in 'the vision' that VI has.<br>
<br>
And on that note, all of your suggestions, comments would require SOE to put forth a great deal of customer service and reprogramming . Aint gonna happen.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gatsuthewarrior>GatsuTheWarrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/10/02 11:33:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2450.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I dont think it will ever happen</span><hr size=1> well thanks, i wanted responses that showed thought and not the usual "dude are you  a f$n retard" things that frequent many message boards. I certainly got well thought comments here. Im well aware that the second choice i offered would NEVER happen in the present system. It was an extreme solution. Some random wacky idea that i thought up at the height of a fever perhaps. <br>
<br>
Anyways thanks again to everyone who posted and gave me feedback i really appreciate what you wrote....no if only Verant would do the same.<br>
<br>
Edit: oh by the way when i think of changes im not just thinking about the post 50 crowd as i get the impression that many people talk about, i mean every warrior at every level. I mean really my job from day 1 was to tank and take a beating. Gaining agro and keeping it was a living nightmare and required that all the other classes hold back from what they could do so i could feel helpful. At least thats how it feels sometimes. well nevermind its late and im rambling on.  <p>~Gatsu Bloodbourne, Champion of Clan Twisted.<br>
